Java is a high-level, object-oriented programming language...Example:

```java
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
    }
```

Java runs on the **JVM (Java Virtual Machine)** using the JRE and is developed using the JDK...Example:

```java
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello, World!");
    }
```

C++ programs begin with the main() function. Example:
```cpp
#include<iostream>
int main() {
  std::cout << "Hello, World!";
  return 0;
}
```

Functions are blocks of code designed to perform tasks. Example:
```javascript
function greet(name) {
  console.log('Hello ' + name);
}
greet('Nirmal');
```
